Study Guide CheckList


Compute
EC2: Know uses, instance types, pricing, auto-scaling, and basics of launching/stopping servers.

Lambda: Recognize serverless, pay-per-use, event-driven integrations.

Elastic Beanstalk: App deployment automation, supports multiple languages.


Storage
S3: Object storage, buckets, versioning, durability, common use cases (backups, data lakes, media storage).

EBS: Block storage for EC2, persistence, snapshot backups.

EFS: Managed NFS, scalable file storage for Linux, shared access.



Database
RDS: Managed SQL (Postgres, MySQL, etc.), backups, scaling, multi-AZ.

DynamoDB: Managed NoSQL, fast, scalable, pay-per-request.

Redshift: Data warehouse, analytics, BI integrations.



Networking & Content Delivery
VPC: Isolated network, subnets, security groups, NAT gateway.

CloudFront: CDN, speeds up static/dynamic content delivery globally.

ELB (Elastic Load Balancer): High availability, balances incoming traffic.

Route 53: DNS, health checks, domain registration.



Security & Identity
IAM: Users/groups/roles, permissions and policies, principle of least privilege.

KMS: Key management and encryption basics.

WAF/Shield: DDoS and web attack protections.



Monitoring & Management
CloudWatch: Log/metric collection, alarms, monitoring dashboards.

CloudTrail: API activity auditing, resource change tracking.

Trusted Advisor: Best practice checks (security, cost, performance).



Messaging & Integration
SNS: Pub-sub notifications and alerts.

SQS: Message queue for distributed processing.

Step Functions: Serverless workflow orchestration basics.

Global Infrastructure: Regions, Availability Zones, Edge Locations.


Security Model: Shared responsibility, basic compliance hints.


Billing Basics: On-demand vs. reserved pricing; cost management tools (Cost Explorer, Budgets).